  "synopsis": "Who knew that even a stationary plant could be surprisingly capable?! \n\nOur protagonist is a saint—or was, until she was betrayed by one of her fellow saint apprentices as well as her fiancé, a hero.\nIn her final moments, she recalls her previous life, when she was just a normal Japanese high school girl, but that doesn't help the fact that she's being eaten alive by a massive plant monster. \n\nAnd yet, by a stroke of luck, she doesn't die for good, but instead reincarnates as said plant monster. With the upper half of a human and the lower half of a plant, she must now spend her life as an Alraune. \n\nAnd so, she tries to live the peaceful life of a plant, photosynthesizing all day!\nWelcome to the diary of a plant girl who just wants some peace and quiet, but something always gets in her way!",
